-- Colombia Stock Movers: Ecopetrol, Canacol Energy Are Active
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-04-02T20:57:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/colombia-stock-movers-ecopetrol-canacol-energy-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  was little changed at 15,038.71, while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  fell 0.1 percent to 1,741.76.  Energy producers rose as oil gained after a report showed
that manufacturing in the U.S. expanded at a faster pace than
forecast, signaling economic growth in the world’s biggest
crude-consuming country.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest  oil company ,
gained 1.8 percent to 5,530 pesos.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based oil
company that operates fields in Colombia, advanced 1.4 percent
to 1,420 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
